S'Culture'
p194
sg12
(lp195
VThe aboriginal culture of Hawaii is Polynesian. Hawaii represents the northernmost extension of the vast Polynesian Triangle of the south and central Pacific Ocean. While traditional Hawaiian culture remains as vestiges in modern Hawaiian society, there are re-enactments of the ceremonies and traditions throughout the islands. Some of these cultural influences, including the popularity (in greatly modified form) of "l\u016bau" and "hula", are strong enough to affect the wider United States.
p196
asa(dp197
g9
I1
