S'Japan'
p689
sg12
(lp690
VThe earliest works of history produced in Japan were the "Rikkokushi", a corpus of six national histories covering the history of Japan from its mythological beginnings until the 9th century. The first of these works were the "Nihon Shoki", compiled by Prince Toneri in 720.
p691
