(lp1056
VThe word "holiday" comes from the Old English word "h\u0101ligdæg" ("h\u0101lig" "holy" + "dæg" "day"). The word originally referred only to special religious days. In modern use, it means any special day of rest or relaxation, as opposed to normal days away from work or school.
