VHaiti's climate is tropical with some variation depending on altitude. Port-au-Prince ranges in January from an average minimum of to an average maximum of ; in July, from . The rainfall pattern is varied, with rain heavier in some of the lowlands and on the northern and eastern slopes of the mountains.
p3771
aVPort-au-Prince receives an average annual rainfall of . There are two rainy seasons, April\u2013June and October\u2013November. Haiti is subject to periodic droughts and floods, made more severe by deforestation. Hurricanes are also a menace.
